12/19/22, 7:13 PM - Ananya: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* next;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n=new node(val);
    node* temp=head;

    if(head==NULL){
        head=n;
    }
    
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
}

void display (node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"->";
    }
}

int main() {

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    display(head);

}

12/19/22, 8:10 PM - Ananya: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* next;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n=new node(val);
    node* temp=head;

    if(head==NULL){
        head=n;
        return;
    }
    
    
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
}

void deletion(node* &head, int del){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next->data!=del){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=temp->next->next;
    
}

void display (node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next==NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"->";
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    cout<<temp->data;
    
}

int main() {

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    deletion(head, 3);
    display(head);

}

using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* next;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n=new node(val);
    node* temp=head;

    if(head==NULL){
        head=n;
        return;
    }
    
    
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
}

void deletion(node* &head, int del){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next->data!=del){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=temp->next->next;
    
}

void display (node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"->";
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    cout<<temp->data;
    
}

int main() {

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    deletion(head, 3);
    display(head);

}

12/19/22, 8:54 PM - A.K Soni: Head wala ho jayega
12/19/22, 8:54 PM - Ananya: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* next;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtHead(node* &head, int val){
    node* n=new node(val);
    n->next=head->next;
    head=n;
}

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n=new node(val);
    node* temp=head;

    if(head==NULL){
        head=n;
        return;
    }
    
    
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
}

void deletion(node* &head, int del){

    if(head==NULL){
        return;
    }
    
    if(head->data==del){
        head=head->next;
        return;
    }

    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next->data!=del){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=temp->next->next;
    
}

void display (node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"->";
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    cout<<temp->data;
    
}

int main() {

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    insertAtHead(head, 0);
    deletion(head, 1);
    display(head);

}

12/22/22, 11:13 PM - Ananya: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* previous;
    node* next;

    node (int val){
        data=val;
        previous=NULL;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n= new node(val);
    node* temp = head;
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
    n->previous=temp;

}

void display(node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"-><-";
        temp=temp->next;
    } 
    cout<<temp->data<<endl;
}

int main(){

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    display(head);

}

12/23/22, 12:40 AM - A.K Soni: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* previous;
    node* next;

    node (int val){
        data=val;
        previous=NULL;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n= new node(val);
    node* temp = head;
    if (head==NULL){
        head=n;
        return;
    }
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
    n->previous=temp;

}

void display(node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"-><-";
        temp=temp->next;
    } 
}

int main(){

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    display(head);

}
12/23/22, 12:50 AM - A.K Soni: void deletenode(node* &head, int val){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next->data!=val){
        temp=temp->next;
    }temp->next->next->previous=temp;
    temp->next=temp->next->next;
}

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* previous;
    node* next;

    node (int val){
        data=val;
        previous=NULL;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n= new node(val);
    node* temp = head;
    if (head==NULL){
        head=n;
        return;
    }
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
    n->previous=temp;

}

void deletion(node* &head, int del){
    node* temp=head;
     
    if(head==NULL){
        return;
    }

    while(temp->data!=del){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->previous->next=temp->next;
    temp->next->previous=temp->previous;
}

void display(node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"-><-";
        temp=temp->next;
    } 
}

using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* previous;
    node* next;

    node (int val){
        data=val;
        previous=NULL;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n= new node(val);
    node* temp = head;
    if (head==NULL){
        head=n;
        return;
    }
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
    n->previous=temp;

}
void deletion(node* &head, int val){
    node* temp=head;
        if(head==NULL){
        return;
        }
        if(head->data==val){
            head=head->next;
            head->previous=NULL;
            return;
        }
    while(temp->next->data!=val){
        temp=temp->next;
    }if(temp->next->next==NULL){
        temp->next=NULL;
        return;
    }
    temp->next->next->previous=temp;
    temp->next=temp->next->next;
}

void display(node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"-><-";
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    cout<<temp->data<<"-><-"<<endl;
    while(temp!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"-><-";
        temp=temp->previous;
    }
    
}

int main(){

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    deletion(head,3);
    display(head);

}

using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* previous;
    node* next;

    node (int val){
        data=val;
        previous=NULL;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n= new node(val);
    node* temp = head;
    if (head==NULL){
        head=n;
        return;
    }
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    temp->next=n;
    n->previous=temp;

}
void deletion(node* &head, int val){
    node* temp=head;
        if(head==NULL){
        return;
        }
        if(head->data==val){
            head=head->next;
            head->previous=NULL;
            return;
        }
    while(temp->next->data!=val){
        temp=temp->next;
    }if(temp->next==NULL){
        temp->previous->next=NULL;
        return;
    }
    temp->next->next->previous=temp;
    temp->next=temp->next->next;
}



void display(node* head){
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<"-><-";
        temp=temp->next;
    } 
}

int main(){

    node* head=NULL;
    insertAtTail(head, 1);
    insertAtTail(head, 2);
    insertAtTail(head, 3);
    // deletion(head, 2);
    deletion(head, 3);
    display(head);

}
12/23/22, 1:52 AM - A.K Soni: void appendK(node * head,int k){
    k=k-1;
    node* temp=head;
    node*end=NULL;
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }end=temp;
    head->previous=end;
    end->next=head;
    while(k--){
        temp=temp->previous;
    }head=temp;
    head->previous=NULL;
}

12/23/22, 2:30 AM - A.K Soni: int findIntersection(node* head1,node* head2){
    node* temp1=head1; node* temp2=head2;
    while(temp1->next!=NULL){
        temp1=temp1->next;
    }while(temp2->next!=NULL){
        temp2=temp2->next;
    }int k=-1;
    while(temp1->data==temp2->data){
        k=temp1->data;
        temp1=temp1->previous;
        temp2=temp2->previous;
    }return k;
}

12/23/22, 2:31 AM - A.K Soni: int findIntersection(node* head1,node* head2){
    node* temp1=head1; node* temp2=head2;
    while(temp1->next!=NULL){
        temp1=temp1->next;
    }while(temp2->next!=NULL){
        temp2=temp2->next;
    }
    while(temp1->data==temp2->data){
        temp1=temp1->previous;
        temp2=temp2->previous;
    }return temp1->next->data;
}

12/23/22, 2:54 AM - A.K Soni: node* mergeTwoInSorted(node* head1, node* head2){
    node* temp1=head1; node* temp2=head2; node* ans=NULL;
    while(temp1->next!=NULL && temp2->next!=NULL){
        if(temp1->data>temp2->data){
            insertAtTail(ans,temp2->data);
            temp2=temp2->next;
        }else{
            insertAtTail(ans,temp1->data);
            temp1=temp1->next;
        }
    }while(temp1->next!=NULL){
        insertAtTail(ans,temp1->data);
        temp1=temp1->next;
    }while(temp2->next!=NULL){
        insertAtTail(ans,temp2->data);
        temp2=temp2->next;
    }return ans;
}

12/23/22, 3:05 AM - A.K Soni: node* mergeTwoInSorted(node* head1, node* head2){
    node* temp1=head1; node* temp2=head2; node* ans=NULL;
    while(temp1!=NULL && temp2!=NULL){
        if(temp1->data>temp2->data){
            insertAtTail(ans,temp2->data);
            temp2=temp2->next;
        }else{
            insertAtTail(ans,temp1->data);
            temp1=temp1->next;
        }
    }while(temp1!=NULL){
        insertAtTail(ans,temp1->data);
        temp1=temp1->next;
    }while(temp2!=NULL){
        insertAtTail(ans,temp2->data);
        temp2=temp2->next;
    }return ans;
}
12/23/22, 3:27 AM - A.K Soni: void insertAtTail(node* &head, int val){
    node* n= new node(val);
    node* temp = head;
    if (head==NULL){
        head=n;
        head->next=head;
        head->previous=head;
        return;
    }while(temp->next!=head){
        temp=temp->next;
    }temp->next=n;
    head->previous=n;
    n->previous=temp;
    n->next=head;
}

12/23/22, 4:11 AM - A.K Soni: node* oddEven(node* head){
    node* temp1=head; node* temp2=head->next; node* ans=NULL;
    while(temp1->next!=head && temp2->next!=head){
        insertAtTail(ans,temp1->data);
        temp1=temp1->next->next; temp2=temp2->next->next;
    }insertAtTail(ans,temp1->data);
    temp1=head;temp2=head->next;
    while(temp1->next!=head && temp2->next!=head){
        insertAtTail(ans,temp2->data);
        temp1=temp1->next->next; temp2=temp2->next->next;
    }insertAtTail(ans,temp2->data);
    return ans;
}

12/23/22, 8:53 PM - A.K Soni: Hello Participants,
This is a reminder mail for the event and also to brief you on some important points that you have to take care during the event.

1. Confirmation mail is your ticket, you'll get the ID card after you will show us that official mail, screenshots not allowed
Without the mail you will not be entertained.

2. If your ID card is lost during the event penalty of Rs.150 will be charged.

3. We have 2 Boarding points for Buses:
 MITS Gole ka Mandir (Arrival time -->  8:00 A.M., Departure time--> 8:15 A.M.)
Railway Station No.1 Police Station (Arrival time--> 8:00 A.M., Departure time--> 8:15 A.M.) Try to reach the points before 5-10 minutes so that you can get the transportation.

4. Please make sure you are in discipline and not violating any rules and do not indulge in ANY ILLEGAL activities. If found anywhere then your registration will be canceled and strict actions will be taken.

5. Please make sure all your assets are with you and are in proper condition. GDG Gwalior, RJIT, and BFS Academy will not be responsible for any loss.

6. Make sure you have your mask and carry a sanitizer with you as your safety will be in your hands.

7. Bring your Aadhar card with you without this you will not be given entry.


Please make sure you are following the above rules and points so that you can enjoy the event properly and when you go back home you have wonderful memories😇.

Venue - BSF Academy, Tekanpur, Gwalior (M.P.) 475005
Location map link - https://maps.app.goo.gl/r4cyqHdKAACiiHqc6

For any queries,

12/26/22, 4:46 PM - Ananya: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class stack{
    public:
    int size;
    int top;
    int* arr;

    stack(){
        size=100;
        top=-1;
        arr= new int[size];
    }
};

bool isEmpty(stack* temp){
    if(temp->top==-1) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull (stack* temp){
    if(temp->top==temp->size-1) return true;
    else return false;
}

void push(stack* &s, int val){
    stack* n = new stack();
    if(isFull(n)) return;
    n->top++;
    n->arr[n->top] = val;
}

int pop(stack* &s){
    stack* temp;
    if(isEmpty(temp)) return -1;
    int item=temp->arr[temp->top];
    temp->top--;
    return item;
}

void(){
    
} 

int main(){
    stack *s = new stack();
    push(s, 2);
    push(s, 3);
    push(s, 4);
    cout<<pop(s)<<endl;
    cout<<isEmpty(s)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull(s)<<endl;
}

12/26/22, 5:05 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;


class stack {

    public:
    int* a;
    int n;
    int top;

    stack(){
        n=100;
        a= new int[n];
        top=-1;
    }

    void push(int val){
        if(top==n-1) cout<<"stack overflow";
        else {
            top++;
            a[top]=val;
        }
    }

    void pop(){
        if(top==-1) cout<<"stack underflow";
        else{
            int item=a[top];
            top--;
        }
    }

    int Top(){
        if(top==-1) {
            cout<<"no element on top"; 
            return -1;
        }
        else return a[top];
    }

    bool empty(){
        if(top==-1) return true;
        else return false;
    }

    void display(){
        for(int i=0; i<=top; i++){
            cout<<a[i];
        } cout<<endl;
    }
};

int main(){

    stack s;
    s.push(2);
    s.push(3);
    s.push(4);
    s.push(5);
    s.display();
    s.pop();
    s.display();
    cout<<s.Top()<<endl;
    cout<<s.empty();

    return 0;

}
12/26/22, 5:17 PM - A.K Soni: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class stack{
    public:
    int size;
    int top;
    int* arr;

    stack(int n){
        size=n;
        top=-1;
        arr= new int[size];
    }
};

bool isEmpty(stack temp){
    if(temp.top==-1) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull (stack temp){
    if(temp.top==temp.size-1) return true;
    else return false;
}

void push(stack& s, int val){
    if(isFull(s)) return;
    s.top++;
    s.arr[s.top] = val;
}

int pop(stack& s){
    if(isEmpty(s)) return -1;
    int item=s.arr[s.top];
    s.top--;
    return item;
}


int main(){
    stack s(4);
    push(s, 2);
    push(s, 3);
    push(s, 4);
    cout<<pop(s)<<endl;
    cout<<isEmpty(s)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull(s)<<endl;
    cout<<pop(s)<<endl;
    cout<<pop(s)<<endl;
    
}

12/26/22, 5:24 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* next;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        next=NULL;
    }

};

// For stack insertion deletion at top ie head

void push(node* &top, int val){
    node* n=new node(val);
    if(n==NULL) {
        cout<<"stack overflow"; //overflow when heap memory is exhausted
        return;
    }
    if(top==NULL){
        top=n; 
        return;
    }
    n->next=top;
    top=n;
}

void pop(node* &top){
    if(top==NULL) {
        cout<<"stack is empty";
        return;
    }
    node* todelete= new node(top->data);
    top=top->next;
    delete todelete; //free memory
}

bool empty(node* top){
    return top==NULL;
}

bool full(node* top, int val){
    node* n = new node(val);
    if(n==NULL) return true;
}

int Top(node* top){
    if(top==NULL) return -1;
    return top->data;
}

void display(node* top){
    node* temp;
    while(temp!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<" ";
        temp=temp->next;
    } cout<<temp->data<<endl;
}


int main(){
    node* top; //top=head
    push(top, 2);
    push(top, 3);
    push(top, 4);
    push(top, 5);
    display(top);
    pop(top);
    display(top);
    cout<<Top(top)<<endl;
    cout<<empty(top)<<endl;
    cout<<full(top, 9)<<endl;
}

12/27/22, 3:52 PM - Ananya: #include <iostream>
#include<string>
using namespace std;

class stack{
    public:
    int size;
    int top;
    char* arr;

    stack(int n){
        size=n;
        top=-1;
        arr= new char[size];
    }
};

bool isEmpty(stack* temp){
    if(temp->top==-1) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull (stack* temp){
    if(temp->top==temp->size-1) return true;
    else return false;
}

void push(stack* s, int val){
    if(isFull(s)) return;
    s->top++;
    s->arr[s->top] = val;
}

int pop(stack* temp){
    // stack* temp;
    if(isEmpty(temp)) return -1;
    int item=temp->arr[temp->top];
    temp->top--;
    return item;
} 

int peek (stack* s, int i){
    if(s->top-i+1<0) return -1;
    else return s->arr[s->top-i+1];
}

int prec (char c){
    if(c=='+'||c=='-') return 1;
    else if(c=='*'||c=='/') return 2;
    else return 0;
}

int isoperator(char o){
    if(o=='+'|| o=='-'|| o=='*'|| o=='/'){
        return 1;
    }
    else return 0;
}

char* InfixToPostfix(stack* s, char* in){
    char* pos=new char[in.size()+1];
    int i=0;
    int j=0;
    while(in[i]!='\0'){
        if(!isoperator(in[i])){
            pos[j]=in[i];
            i++; j++;
        }
        else{
            if(prec(in[i])>prec(s->arr[s->top])) { 
                push(s, in[i]); i++;
            }
            else{
                pos[j]=pop(s);
                j++;
            }
        }
    }
    while(!isEmpty(s)){
        pos[j]=pop(s);
        j++;
    } 
    pos[j]='\0';
    return pos;
}

int main(){
    stack *s = new stack(10);
    char* infix="a+b*c+d/e";
    cout<<InfixToPostfix(s, infix);

}

12/28/22, 9:17 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class queue {
    public:
    int n;
    int* arr;
    int front;
    int rear;

    queue(int a){
        int n=a;
        front=0;
        rear=0;
        arr=new int[n];
    }
};

// in circular queue, we will take front as the index before the first element, because if we take it as the first element then we can't find condition for empty.

bool isEmpty(queue* q){
    if(q->front==q->rear) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull(queue* q){
    if((q->rear+1)% q->n==q->front) return true;
    else return false;
}

void enqueue(queue* q, int val){
    if(isFull(q)) {
        cout<<"queue overflow";
        return;
    }
    q->rear=(q->rear+1)%q->n;  //increament rear 
    q->arr[q->rear]=val;
    
}

void dequeue(queue *q){
    if(isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"queue underflow";
        return;
    }
    q->front=(q->front+1)%q->n;
}

void peek(queue* q){
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"empty";
        return;
    }
    cout<<"element: "<<q->arr[q->front+1]<<" ";
    cout<<"index:"<<q->front+1;
    return;
}

void display(queue* q){ 
    if(isEmpty(q)) return;
    for(int i=(q->front+1)%q->n; i!=q->rear; i=(i+1)%q->n){
        cout<<q->arr[q->front+1]<<" ";
        q->front++;
    } cout<<q->arr[q->rear]<<endl;
}

int main(){
    queue* q = new queue(6);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);
    enqueue(q, 4);
    enqueue(q, 5);
    enqueue(q, 6);
    dequeue(q);
    enqueue(q,7);
    enqueue(q, 8);
    enqueue(q, 9);
    peek(q);
    cout<<endl<<isEmpty(q)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull(q)<<endl;
    display(q);
}

12/28/22, 9:32 PM - A.K Soni: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class queue {
    public:
    int n;
    int* arr;
    int front;
    int rear;

    queue(int a){
        int n=a;
        front=0;
        rear=0;
        arr=new int[n];
    }
};

// in circular queue, we will take front as the index before the first element, because if we take it as the first element then we can't find condition for empty.

bool isEmpty(queue* q){
    if(q->front==q->rear) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull(queue* q){
    if((q->rear+1)% q->n==q->front) return true;
    else return false;
}

void enqueue(queue* q, int val){
    if(isFull(q)) {
        cout<<"queue overflow";
        return;
    }
    q->rear=(q->rear+1)%q->n;  //increament rear 
    q->arr[q->rear]=val;
    
}

void dequeue(queue *q){
    if(isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"queue underflow";
        return;
    }
    q->front=(q->front+1)%q->n;
}

void peek(queue* q){
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"empty";
        return;
    }
    cout<<"element: "<<q->arr[q->front+1]<<" ";
    cout<<"index:"<<q->front+1;
    return;
}

void display(queue* q){ 
    if(isEmpty(q)) return;
    for(int i=(q->front+1)%q->n; i!=q->rear; i=(i+1)%q->n){
        cout<<q->arr[q->front+1]<<" ";
        q->front++;
    } cout<<q->arr[q->rear]<<endl;
}

int main(){
    queue* q = new queue(6);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);
    enqueue(q, 4);
    enqueue(q, 5);
    enqueue(q, 6);
    dequeue(q);
    enqueue(q,7);
    enqueue(q, 8);
    enqueue(q, 9);
    enqueue(q, 9);
    enqueue(q, 9);
    enqueue(q, 9);
    enqueue(q, 9);
    peek(q);
    cout<<endl<<isEmpty(q)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull(q)<<endl;
    display(q);
}

12/29/22, 11:14 AM - A.K Soni: # include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class cqueue{
    public:
    int * arr;
    int front,rare,n;
    cqueue(int x){
        n=x+1;
        arr=new int[n];
        front=0; rare=0;
    }
};
bool isFull(cqueue * q){
    if(q->front==(q->rare+1)%q->n)return true;
    return false;
}

bool isEmpty(cqueue * q){
    if(q->front==q->rare)return true;
    return false;
}
void enqueue(cqueue * q,int val){
    if(!isFull(q)){
        q->rare=(q->rare+1)%q->n;
        q->arr[q->rare]=val;
    }else cout<<"queue is full"<<endl;
}
void dequeue(cqueue *q){
    if(!isEmpty(q))
        q->front=(q->front+1)%q->n;
    else cout<<"queue is empty"<<endl;
}
int peek(cqueue * q){
    if(!isEmpty(q))
    return q->arr[(q->front+1)%q->n];
    return -1;
}
void display(cqueue * s){
    if(!isEmpty(s)){
    int n=s->front;
    while(s->front!=s->rare){
        cout<<s->arr[(s->front+1)%s->n]<<" ";
        s->front=(s->front+1)%s->n;
    }s->front=n;
    }else cout<<"empty Queue"<<endl;
}

int main(){
    cqueue * q=new cqueue(6);
    enqueue(q,1);
    enqueue(q,2);
    enqueue(q,3);
    enqueue(q,4);
    enqueue(q,5);
    enqueue(q,6);
    enqueue(q,7);
    dequeue(q);
    display(q);
    enqueue(q,7);
    enqueue(q,7);
    enqueue(q,7);
    display(q);
}

12/29/22, 12:04 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class queue {
    public:
    int n;
    int* arr;
    int front;
    int rear;

    queue(int a){
        int n=a+1;
        front=0;
        rear=0;
        arr=new int[n];
    }
};

bool isEmpty(queue* q){
    if(q->front==q->rear) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull(queue* q){
    if((q->rear+1)% q->n==q->front) return true;
    else return false;
}

void enqueue(queue* q, int val){
    if(isFull(q)) {
        cout<<"queue overflow";
        return;
    }
    q->rear=(q->rear+1)%q->n;  
    q->arr[q->rear]=val;
}

void dequeue(queue *q){
    if(isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"queue underflow";
        return;
    }
    q->front=(q->front+1)%q->n;
}

void peek(queue* q){
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"empty";
        return;
    }
    cout<<"element: "<<q->arr[(q->front+1)%q->n]<<" ";
    cout<<"index:"<<q->front+1;
    return;
}

void display(queue* q){ 
    if(isEmpty(q)) return;
    for(int i=(q->front+1)%q->n; i!=q->rear; i=(i+1)%q->n){
        cout<<q->arr[(q->front+1)%q->n]<<" ";
        q->front=(q->front+1)%q->n;
    } 
    // cout<<q->arr[q->rear]<<endl;
}

int main(){
    queue* q = new queue(6);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);
    enqueue(q, 4);
    enqueue(q, 5);
    enqueue(q, 6);
    enqueue(q, 7);
    enqueue(q, 8);
    enqueue(q, 9);
    peek(q);
    cout<<endl<<isEmpty(q)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull(q)<<endl;
    display(q);
}

using namespace std;

class queue {
    public:
    int n;
    int* arr;
    int front;
    int rear;

    queue(int a){
        n=a+1;
        front=0;
        rear=0;
        arr=new int[n];
    }
};

bool isEmpty(queue* q){
    if(q->front==q->rear) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull(queue* q){
    if((q->rear+1)% q->n==q->front) return true;
    else return false;
}

void enqueue(queue* q, int val){
    if(isFull(q)) {
        cout<<"queue overflow";
        return;
    }
    else {q->rear=(q->rear+1)%q->n;  
    q->arr[q->rear]=val;}
}

void dequeue(queue *q){
    if(isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"queue underflow";
        return;
    }
    q->front=(q->front+1)%q->n;
}

void peek(queue* q){
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        cout<<"empty";
        return;
    }
    cout<<"element: "<<q->arr[(q->front+1)%q->n]<<" ";
    cout<<"index:"<<q->front+1;
    return;
}

void display(queue* q){ 
    if(isEmpty(q)) return;
    for(int i=(q->front+1)%q->n; i!=q->rear; i=(i+1)%q->n){
        cout<<q->arr[(q->front+1)%q->n]<<" ";
        q->front=(q->front+1)%q->n;
    } 
    cout<<q->arr[q->rear]<<endl;
}

int main(){
    queue* q = new queue(6);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);
    enqueue(q, 4);
    enqueue(q, 5);
    enqueue(q, 6);
    enqueue(q, 7);
    enqueue(q, 8);

}

12/29/22, 1:19 PM - A.K Soni: # include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node*next;
    node(int val){
        data=val;
        next=NULL;
    }
};
bool isEmpty(node* q){
    if (q==NULL)return true;
    return false;
}
void enqueue(node* &head,int val){
    node* v=new node(val);
    if(head==NULL){
        head=v;
        return;
    }
    node* temp=head;
    while(temp->next!=NULL){
        temp=temp->next;
    }temp->next=v;
}
void dequeue(node* &head){
    if(isEmpty(head)){
        cout<<"queue underflow"<<endl;
        return;
    }
    if(head->next==NULL)head=NULL;
    else head=head->next;
}

void display(node * head){
    if(isEmpty(head)){
        cout<<"empty queue"<<endl;
        return;
    }
    node * temp=head;
    while(temp!=NULL){
        cout<<temp->data<<" ";
        temp=temp->next;
    }
}
int main(){
    node* q=NULL;
    enqueue(q,1);
    dequeue(q);
    enqueue(q,2);
    enqueue(q,3);
    enqueue(q,4);
    enqueue(q,5);
    enqueue(q,6);
    enqueue(q,7);
    dequeue(q);
    display(q);
}
12/29/22, 1:20 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class queue {
    public:
    int n;
    int* arr;
    int front;
    int back;

    queue(int n){
        front=-1;
        back=-1;
        arr=new int[n];
    }
};

bool isEmpty(queue* q){
    if(q->front==-1 || q->front>q->back) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull(queue* q){
    if(q->back==q->n-1) return true;
    else return false;
}

void enqueueF(queue* q, int val){
    if(q->back==q->n-1) {
        cout<<"queue overflow";
        return;
    }
    if(q->front==-1) {
        q->front++;
        q->arr[q->front]=val;
        q->back++;
        return;
    }
    int temp;
    temp=q->front;
    for(int i=temp; i<=q->back; i++){
        int store = q->arr[temp];
        q->arr[temp+1]=store;
        temp++;
    }
    q->back++;
    q->arr[q->front]=val;
}

void enqueueR(queue* q, int val){
    if(q->back==q->n-1) {
        cout<<"queue overflow";
        return;
    }
    q->back++;
    q->arr[q->back]=val;
    if(q->front==-1) {
        q->front++;
    }
}

void dequeueF(queue *q){
    if(q->front==-1 || q->front>q->back) {
        cout<<"queue underflow";
        return;
    }
    q->front++;
}

int peek(queue* q, int pos){
    if (q->front==-1 || q->front>q->back) return -1;
    return q->arr[q->front];
}

void display(queue* q){ 
    if(isEmpty(q)) return;
    for(int i=q->front; i<=q->back; i++){
        cout<<q->arr[q->front]<<" ";
        q->front++;
    } cout<<endl;
}

int main(){
    queue* q = new queue(4);
    enqueueR(q, 2);
    enqueueR(q, 3);
    enqueueR(q, 4);
    dequeueF(q);
    enqueueF(q, 8);
    enqueueF(q, 9);
    cout<<peek(q, 1)<<endl;
    cout<<isEmpty(q)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull(q)<<endl;
    display(q);
}

12/29/22, 1:24 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class node {
    public:
    int data;
    node* next;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        next=NULL;
    }
};

bool isEmpty(node* front){
    if(front==NULL) return true;
    else return false;
}

bool isFull(){
    node* n = new node(8);
    if(n==NULL) return true;
    else return false;
}

void enqueue(node* &front, node*&rear, int val){
    node* n= new node(val);
    if(n==NULL) {
        cout<<"queue overflow"<<endl;
        return;
    }
    else if(front==NULL){
        front=n;
        rear=n;
        return;
    }
    else {
        rear->next = n;
        rear=n;
    }    
}


void dequeue (node* &front, node*&rear){
    if(front==NULL){
        cout<<"queue underflow"<<endl;
        return;
    }
    if(front==rear){
        rear=NULL;
        front==NULL;
        return;
    }
    front=front->next;
}

void display(node* front){
    cout<<"printing ele: "<<endl;
    while(front!=NULL){
        cout<<front->data<<"->";
        front=front->next;
    }
}

int main(){
    node* front=NULL;
    node* rear=NULL;
    cout<<isEmpty(front)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull()<<endl;
    enqueue(front, rear, 2);
    enqueue(front, rear, 3);
    enqueue(front, rear, 4);
    enqueue(front, rear, 5);
    dequeue(front, rear);
    display(front);
    cout<<isEmpty(front)<<endl;
    cout<<isFull()<<endl;
}

12/29/22, 2:07 PM - A.K Soni: #include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class DEqueue {
    public:
    int n;
    int* arr;
    int front;
    int back;

    DEqueue(int x){
        n=x;
        front=-1;
        back=-1;
        arr=new int[n];
    }
};

void enqueueF(DEqueue* &q,int val){
    if(q->front==-1){
        q->arr[++q->back]=val;
        q->front++; return;
    }int i=q->back;
    if(i+1>=q->n){
            cout<<"queue full"<<endl;
            return;
    }
    while(i>=0){
        q->arr[i+1]=q->arr[i];i--;
    }q->arr[0]=val;++q->back;
}
void enqueueB(DEqueue* &q,int val){
    if((q->back+1)>=q->n){
        cout<<"queue full"<<endl; return;
    }q->arr[++q->back]=val;
}
void dequeueB(DEqueue *& q){
    if(q->back==-1){
        cout<<"empty queue"<<endl; return;
    }q->back=q->back-1;
}
void dequeueF(DEqueue*& q){
    if(q->back==-1){
        cout<<"empty queue"<<endl; return;
    }int i=0;
    while(i<q->back){
        q->arr[i]=q->arr[i++];
    }q->back=q->back-1;
}

void display(DEqueue*q){
    int i=0;
    if(q->back==-1){
        cout<<"empty queue"<<endl;
        return;
    }
    while(i<=q->back){
        cout<<q->arr[i++]<<" ";
    }
}

int main(){
    DEqueue* q=new DEqueue(6);
    enqueueB(q,2);
    enqueueB(q,3);
    enqueueB(q,3);
    enqueueB(q,4);
    enqueueB(q,5);
    enqueueB(q,6);
    enqueueB(q,7);
    display(q);
}

12/29/22, 2:25 PM - A.K Soni: #include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class DEqueue {
    public:
    int n;
    int* arr;
    int back;

    DEqueue(int x){
        n=x;
        back=-1;
        arr=new int[n];
    }
};

bool isEmpty(DEqueue* q){
    if(q->back==-1)return true;
    return false;
}
bool isFull(DEqueue* q){
    if(q->back+1>=q->n)return true;
    return false;
}

void enqueueF(DEqueue* &q,int val){
    if(q->back==-1){
        q->arr[++q->back]=val;
        return;
    }int i=q->back;
    if(isFull(q)){
            cout<<"queue full"<<endl;
            return;
    }
    while(i>=0){
        q->arr[i+1]=q->arr[i];i--;
    }q->arr[0]=val;++q->back;
}
void enqueueB(DEqueue* &q,int val){
    if(isFull(q)){
        cout<<"queue full"<<endl; return;
    }q->arr[++q->back]=val;
}
void dequeueB(DEqueue *& q){
    if(isEmpty(q)){
        cout<<"empty queue"<<endl; return;
    }q->back=q->back-1;
}
void dequeueF(DEqueue*& q){
    if(isEmpty(q)){
        cout<<"empty queue"<<endl; return;
    }int i=0;
    while(i<q->back){
        q->arr[i]=q->arr[++i];
    }q->back=q->back-1;
}
int peekF(DEqueue*q){
    if(!isEmpty(q))
    return q->arr[0];
    return -1;
}
int peekB(DEqueue*q){
    if(!isEmpty(q))
    return q->arr[q->back];
    return -1;
}


void display(DEqueue*q){
    int i=0;
    if(isEmpty(q)){
        cout<<"empty queue"<<endl;
        return;
    }
    while(i<=q->back){
        cout<<q->arr[i++]<<" ";
    }
}

int main(){
    DEqueue* q=new DEqueue(6);
    enqueueB(q,2);
    enqueueB(q,3);
    enqueueB(q,3);
    dequeueF(q);
    enqueueB(q,4);
    enqueueB(q,5);
    enqueueB(q,6);
    enqueueB(q,7);
    enqueueF(q,7);
    display(q);
    cout<<endl;
    cout<<peekF(q)<<" "<<peekB(q) ;
}

12/30/22, 2:26 PM - Ananya: Rukoo
12/30/22, 2:26 PM - Ananya: #include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class que{
    stack<int> s1;

    public:
    void enqueue(int x){
        s1.push(x);
    }
    int dequeue(){
        if(s1.empty()) {
            cout<<"queue empty";
            return -1;
        }
        else{
            int x= s1.top();
            s1.pop();
            while(s1.empty()){
                return x;
            } 
            int item = dequeue();
            s1.push(x);
            return item;
        }
    }
};

int main(){
    que q;
    q.enqueue(2);
    q.enqueue(3);
    q.enqueue(4);
    cout<<q.dequeue()<<endl;
    q.enqueue(5);
    cout<<q.dequeue()<<endl;
    cout<<q.dequeue()<<endl;
    cout<<q.dequeue()<<endl;
    cout<<q.dequeue()<<endl;
}

1/2/23, 1:59 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* left;
    node* right;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        left=NULL;
        right=NULL;
    }
};

void preorderTraversal (node* root){
    if(root==NULL) return;
    cout<<root->data<<" ";
    preorderTraversal(root->left);
    preorderTraversal(root->right);
}

void inorderTraversal (node* root){
    if(root==NULL) return;
    preorderTraversal(root->left);
    cout<<root->data<<" ";
    preorderTraversal(root->right);
}

void postorderTraversal (node* root){
    if(root==NULL) return;
    preorderTraversal(root->left);
    preorderTraversal(root->right);
    cout<<root->data<<" ";
}

int main(){
    node* root = new node(1);
    root->left = new node(2);
    root->right= new node(3);
    root->left->left = new node(4);
    root->left->right = new node(6);
    root->right->left= new node(5);
    root->right->right = new node(7);
    preorderTraversal(root);
    cout<<endl;
    inorderTraversal(root);
    cout<<endl;
    postorderTraversal(root);
    cout<<endl;
}

using namespace std;

int hcf(int a,int b){
    while(a!=b){
        if(a>b){
            a=a-b;
        }else b=b-a;
    }return a;
}

int main() {
	// your code goes here
	int t; cin>>t;
	while(t--){
	    int a,b; cin>>a>>b;
	    cout<<hcf(a,b)<<endl;;
	}
	return 0;
}

1/6/23, 1:57 PM - Ananya: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
    public:
    int data;
    node* left;
    node* right;

    node(int val){
        data=val;
        left=NULL;
        right=NULL;
    }
};

void preorderTraversal (node* root){
    if(root==NULL) return;
    cout<<root->data<<" ";
    preorderTraversal(root->left);
    preorderTraversal(root->right);
}

void inorderTraversal (node* root){
    if(root==NULL) return;
    inorderTraversal(root->left);
    cout<<root->data<<" ";
    inorderTraversal(root->right);
}

void postorderTraversal (node* root){
    if(root==NULL) return;
    postorderTraversal(root->left);
    postorderTraversal(root->right);
    cout<<root->data<<" ";
}

int isBST(node* root){
    node* prev;
    prev=NULL;
    if(root==NULL) return 0;
    else{
        if(!isBST(root->left)) return 0;
        if(prev->data <= root->data && prev!=NULL) return 0;
        prev=root;
        return isBST(root->right);
    }

}

int search (node* root, int key){
    if(root==NULL) return -1;
    if(root->data==key) return root->data;
    else if(key> root->data) return search(root->right, key);
    else return search(root->left, key);
}

int itterativeSearch (node* root, int key){
    while(root!=NULL){
        if(key==root->data) return root->data;
        else if(key > root->data) root=root->right;
        else root=root->left;
    }
    return -1;
}

void insertBST(node* root, int key){
    node* n = new node(key);
    node* temp = NULL;
    while(root!=NULL){
        temp=root;
        if(key==root->data) {
            cout<<"no duplicates allowed";
            return;
        }
        else if(key>root->data){
            if(temp->right==NULL) {
                temp->right=n;
            }
            root= root->right;

        }
        else {
            if(temp->left==NULL){
                temp->left=n;
            }
            root=root->left;
        }
    }
    return;
}

int main(){
    node* root = new node(7);
    root->left = new node(5);
    root->right= new node(10);
    root->left->left = new node(2);
    root->left->right = new node(6);
    root->right->left= new node(9);
    root->right->right = new node(11);
    preorderTraversal(root);
    cout<<endl;
    inorderTraversal(root);
    cout<<endl;
    postorderTraversal(root);
    cout<<endl;
    cout<<isBST(root)<<endl;
    cout<<search(root, 2)<<endl;
    cout<<itterativeSearch(root, 2)<<endl;
    insertBST(root, 4);

}

1/31/23, 10:26 PM - A.K Soni: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ll long long int
#define vi vector<int>
#define vii vector<pair<int,int>>
#define mii map<int,int>
#define mci map<char,int>
#define sort(k) sort(k.begin(),k.end())
#define rep(i,x) for(auto i:x)
const int N=10e5+10;

void encryption(){
    string ans="abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
    vector<char>v;
    string t;cout<<"enter plain text: "; cin>>t;
    for(int i=0;i<t.length();i++){
        int q=(int(t[i])-94)%26;
        v.push_back(ans[q]);
    }cout<<"cipher text: ";
    for( auto i:v){
        cout<<i;
    }
}

void decryption(){
    string ans="abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
    vector<char>v;
    string t;cout<<"enter plain text: "; cin>>t;
    for(int i=0;i<t.length();i++){
        int q=(int(t[i])-100)%26;
        v.push_back(ans[q]);
    }cout<<"cipher text: ";
    for( auto i:v){
        cout<<i;
    }
}

int main(){
    decryption();

}

1/31/23, 10:27 PM - A.K Soni: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ll long long int
#define vi vector<int>
#define vii vector<pair<int,int>>
#define mii map<int,int>
#define mci map<char,int>
#define sort(k) sort(k.begin(),k.end())
#define rep(i,x) for(auto i:x)
const int N=10e5+10;


int main(){
    string ans="abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
    vector<char>v;
    string k;cout<<"enter key: "; cin>>k;
    string t;cout<<"enter plain text: "; cin>>t;
    int j=0;
    for(int i=0;i<t.length();i++){
        if(j>=k.length())j=0;
        int q=(int(t[i])-97+int(k[j])-97)%26;
        v.push_back(ans[q]);
        j++;
    }cout<<"cipher text: ";
    for( auto i:v){
        cout<<i;
    }
}
